						<summary>

						<p>On a slab set up in a field to the north of the village.</p>						

						<p>Bukka I, 1367 A.D.</p>						

						<p>This inscription is dated <hi rend="bold">Śaka 1289, Plavaṅga, Āśvija śu. 1, Saturday</hi> corresponding to <hi rend="bold">1367 A.D., September 25.</hi></p>						

						<p>The inscription records a grant of one <hi rend="italic">puṭṭi</hi> of land irrigated by the tank at Pāntarlapalle by Bammi-nāyuḍu, son of Pāpi-nāyuḍu, for food offerings to God Ahōbaladēva of Kadiri.</p>						

						</summary>
